		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2011"></a><br><code>sle2011/paper01</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2011</a> paper:</span><br><i>A Dedicated Language for Context Composition and Execution of True Black-Box Model Transformations</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/AndreasSeibel.html">Andreas Seibel</a>, <a href="../profile/ReginaHebig.html">Regina Hebig</a>, <a href="../profile/StefanNeumann.html">Stefan Neumann</a>, <a href="../profile/HolgerGiese.html">Holger Giese</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_2">10.1007/978-3-642-28830-2_2</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagM">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> The work introduces a composition framework for coordinating heterogeneous model transformations as black boxes.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3b.html"><span class="tagL">T3B: Transformation Languages</span></a><ul><li> It targets composition across different model transformation languages and engines.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5g.html"><span class="tagL">T5G: Traceability</span></a><ul><li> Traceability is explicitly part of the problem setting and keywords, to relate composed transformations and results.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6b.html"><span class="tagL">T6B: Industrial</span></a><ul><li> The approach is illustrated on an industrial case study.
</li></ul></li></ul>
